.nh
.TH "prayertime-cli" "1" "Mar 2026" "prayertime-cli" ""

.SH NAME
prayertime-cli-times-get - Fetch prayer times for a location and date


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBprayertime-cli times get [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch one day's prayer schedule for a resolved place or explicit coordinates.

.PP
MVP 1 is stateless, so every call must include --query PLACE or both --lat and --lon. Use --field with --quiet for one scalar value, or --json for the full structured response.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--country-code\fP=""
	Optional ISO country code filter

.PP
\fB--date\fP="today"
	Date in YYYY-MM-DD format or 'today'

.PP
\fB--field\fP=""
	Return one field such as maghrib, iftar, yatsi, timezone, or method_name

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for get

.PP
\fB--lat\fP=0
	Latitude coordinate. Use with --lon instead of --query

.PP
\fB--lon\fP=0
	Longitude coordinate. Use with --lat instead of --query

.PP
\fB--query\fP=""
	Place name to resolve. Required unless --lat and --lon are set

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Emit only the selected field value


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Emit structured JSON to stdout


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
prayertime-cli times get --query Istanbul
prayertime-cli times get --query Ankara --country-code TR --field yatsi --quiet
prayertime-cli times get --lat 41.01384 --lon 28.94966 --date 2026-03-07 --json
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBprayertime-cli-times(1)\fP
